code.originalText:
Definition: Description: A characteristic of an oral solid dosage form of a medicinal product, specifying the two dimensional
            representation of the solid dose form, in terms of the outside perimeter of a solid dosage form when the dosage form, resting on a flat
            surface, is viewed from directly above, including slight rounding of corners. SPLSHAPE does not include embossing, scoring, debossing, or
            internal cut-outs. SPLSHAPE is independent of the orientation of the imprint and logo. Shapes can include: Triangle (3 sided); Square;
            Round; Semicircle; Pentagon (5 sided); Diamond; Double circle; Bullet; Hexagon (6 sided); Rectangle; Gear; Capsule; Heptagon (7 sided);
            Trapezoid; Oval; Clover; Octagon (8 sided); Tear; Freeform.
